Gradient Descent Calculation¶

In [2]:
# Extract the gdp per country and the life satisfaction score from dataframe
x = df["GDP"]
y = df["Value"]
In [3]:
# Step 1: Rescale data and reshape array for matrix calculations
x = (x - x.mean()) / x.std()
x = np.c_[np.ones(x.shape[0]), x]
In [4]:
# Step 2: Set up variables
alpha = 0.1 #Step size
iterations = 1000 #No. of iterations
m = y.size #No. of data points
np.random.seed(123) #Set the seed
theta = np.random.rand(2) #Pick some random values to start with
In [5]:
def gradient_descent(x, y, theta, iterations, alpha):
    past_costs = []
    past_thetas = [theta]
    for i in range(iterations):
        prediction = np.dot(x, theta)
        error = prediction - y
        cost = 1/(2*m) * np.dot(error.T, error)
        past_costs.append(cost)
        theta = theta - (alpha * (1/m) * np.dot(x.T, error))
        past_thetas.append(theta)
        
    return past_thetas, past_costs
In [6]:
# Pass the relevant variables to the function
past_thetas, past_costs = gradient_descent(x, y, theta, iterations, alpha)
In [7]:
# Evaluate the optimal theta
best_theta = past_thetas[-1].copy()
#Print the results...
print("Gradient Descent optimal parameters are:\n Bias Term (Intercept): {:.2f}\n Slope: {:.2f}".format(best_theta[0], best_theta[1]))

Gradient Descent optimal parameters are:
 Bias Term (Intercept): 6.53
 Slope: 0.54

Animate the Optimal Parameters for Gradient Descent Training Model¶

In [9]:
#Set the plot up,
fig = plt.figure()
ax = plt.axes()
plt.title('GDP and Life Satisfaction Score')
plt.xlabel('Normalized GDP per capita (USD)')
plt.ylabel('Life Satisfaction Score')
plt.scatter(x[:,1], y, color='red')
line, = ax.plot([], [], lw=2)
annotation = ax.text(-1, 7, '')
annotation.set_animated(True)
plt.close()

#Generate the animation data,
def init():
    line.set_data([], [])
    annotation.set_text('')
    return line, annotation

# animation function.  This is called sequentially
def animate(i):
    x = np.linspace(-5, 20, 1000)
    y = past_thetas[i][1]*x + past_thetas[i][0]
    line.set_data(x, y)
    annotation.set_text('Cost = %.2f' % (past_costs[i]))
    return line, annotation

anim = animation.FuncAnimation(fig, animate, init_func=init, frames=300, interval=0, blit=True)

anim.save('animation.gif', writer='imagemagick', fps = 30)
